# LLM gateway provider secrets — template.
#
# Copy to `.env.llm-secrets` (gitignored) and fill in. The llm-gateway sources
# this file (see bin/laptop-bridge.sh `gateway`) and resolves each provider's
# credential from the `credentialEnv` named in `.singularity/llm-providers.json`.
# Only set the keys for providers you've enabled in that catalog.
#
#   cp .env.llm-secrets.example .env.llm-secrets   &&   $EDITOR .env.llm-secrets

# Anthropic — the default provider (alias claude-sonnet-4-6 / claude-haiku-4-5).
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# OpenAI — only if you add an `openai` provider to the catalog.
# OPENAI_API_KEY=

# Copilot — only if you add a `copilot` (OpenAI-compatible) gateway provider.
# This is the gateway-side Copilot LLM, NOT the Copilot CLI executor (that runs
# on the laptop mcp-server via the `copilot` binary + its own auth).
# COPILOT_TOKEN=

# ── Copilot SDLC executor (laptop mcp-server BYOK) ──────────────────────────
# These configure the `copilot_execute` tool's backend and are exported in the
# shell that runs `bin/laptop-bridge.sh mcp` (they pass through to the CLI) —
# they are NOT read from this file by the gateway. Listed here for reference:
#   COPILOT_PROVIDER_TYPE=anthropic
#   COPILOT_PROVIDER_BASE_URL=https://api.anthropic.com
#   COPILOT_PROVIDER_API_KEY=
#   COPILOT_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-6
